sql:
SELECT c.client_name, w.week_date
FROM client_data c, weekly_data w
WHERE c.client_id = 1 AND w.week_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- Engagement metrics are quantitative measures that indicate user interaction with content on social media platforms;
- The most recent reporting date refers to the latest week for which data is available in the dataset;
- Interaction types include likes, comments, shares, etc., which are detailed under the metric_name.

'particular week last summer' refers to the week of August 27, 2012;
'engagement for each type of metric' includes likes, comments, shares, etc.;
'various platforms' refer to different social media platforms like Facebook, Twitter.

'analytics team members' refers to users with the role 'analyst';
'names starting with John' includes all users whose names begin with the letter 'J' and are followed by 'ohn';
'recent Twitter engagement' refers to the latest tweets, replies, and retweets;
'most recent system access' refers to the latest access date, type, IP, and user agent.

sql:
SELECT c.client_name, ca.access_type
FROM client_data c
JOIN client_access ca ON c.client_id = ca.client_id;
